<br><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="1">My cool thing! See, it's this...thing. And it's, like...cool. It's shiny...<br>It has all sorts of moving parts. And it does things. Cool things!</font></div></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/usuperrats.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Super Rats</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/8/02 5:10:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4150.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.happysoda.com/images/keiavi.jpg height=76 width=78></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shaking and Pen Stances.</span><hr size=1> I've heard that about caffiene.<br>
<br>
Do increase the speed of your line.  Just think about it, the less time it takes to draw a line, the less time there is to record a shake...plus the inertia of making the line will be stronger than a shake.  The down side is, you lose quite a bit of accuracy.  You don't need to speed ink (which is bad), but you may want to increase it a little.<br>
<br>
Your posture might have more to do with shakes than how you hold the pen, unless your grabbing it super tight...relax it.  Also, it takes practice to control your muscles like that, so give it some time. <p>=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=<br>
